Huge waves that you can farm and catch up from the income with.
{{sticker:zombie-brand-clap}} 

The point is, some people think they can gain a lead and not take risks to keep it from being turned around.  Riot is potentially changing that, in turn, causing an indirect comeback mechanic.  If you're bad at making those risky plays pay off or think you can play safe after getting ahead, as Sans would say, "You're gonna have a bad time."

I'm just adding to the counterweight. I might be poking in the wrong direction, or be wrong with my assessments completely, but from what  I've seen here, The angry rants have never changed anything.

Riot already said they're pushing a hotfix next week... with Graves nerfs. No Yasuo nerfs. Yasuo is sitting on 54% winrate. So does Graves, but he's under 50% in Diamond+.

{{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}}
